o are predominantly large cap holdings   no one position is to exceed  at the time of purchase stocks are held for an average of  to  years our portfolio is not index driven and does not mimic benchmarks which is the primary reason for gcm’s longterm record of outperformance high income equity portfolio the grisanti capital management high income equity portfolio has three guiding principles  to protect capital in turbulent markets  to provide potential for capital appreciation with a degree of stability and  to generate better than average current income  this conservative approach is designed to deliver a steady return in various market environments  the product is not designed to “keep up with the market” rather this product is designed for investors seeking some equity exposure with less risk and higher income it will tend to outperform the overall market as measured by the sp  index in periods of declining or volatile prices and it will tend to lag behind but still appreciate in sharply rising markets it offers equity exposure with less volatility and a high dividend yield   contact us about us about grisanti history our team contact us large cap value portfolio philosophy  process past quarterly letters high income equity portfolio philosophy  process past quarterly letters in the news grisanti videos articles  third avenue suite c new york ny   copyright   grisanti capital management llc all rights reserved site map      web design and domain names by about grisanti capital management  new york city  grisanti capital management search for home about us about grisanti history our team large cap value portfolio philosophy  process past quarterly letters high income equity portfolio philosophy  process past quarterly letters in the news articles videos bloomberg large cap value commentary st quarter  continue reading high income equity portfolio commentary st quarter  continue reading what makes grisanti capital management different since our founding in  grisan